m also meets the applicable cost threshold). The item has been subject to aberrant billing patterns. (Aberrant billing is suggested when an item with at least 1,000 claims and $1 million in payments during a recent 12-month period shows an unexpected increase in billed claims without explanatory contributing factors (such as new technology or updated coverage policies.) Step 2: CMS Periodically Selects Items from the Master List to Include on One or Both Required Lists: CMS considers factors such as geographic location, item utilization or cost, system capabilities, emerging trends, vulnerabilities identified in official agency reports, or other analysis. Step 3: CMS Issues a Formal Notice. When items from the Master List are added to one or both Required Lists: CMS will announce the item(s) selected and a formal notice period of at least 60 days will begin. Step 4: Requirements Take Effect: Requirements only take effect when the formal notice period ends. Required Lists are generally updated annually but may also be updated on an ad hoc basis per statute.","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":838,"renderedHeight":1678,"naturalWidth":1216,"naturalHeight":2435,"loading":"lazy","decoding":null,"altVerdict":"TOO_LONG","altReason":"alt text is 1308 characters — consider a caption or description","bytes":276222},{"src":"https://www.cms.gov/themes/custom/cms_evo/logo.svg","alt":"CMS.gov","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":167,"renderedHeight":40,"naturalWidth":300,"naturalHeight":72,"loading":null,"decoding":null,"altVerdict":"GOOD","altReason":"present, no red flags","bytes":2084},{"src":"https://www.cms.gov/themes/custom/cms_evo/images/hhslogo.png","alt":"HHS Logo","hasAlt":true,"isDecorative":false,"isMissingAlt":false,"ariaHidden":false,"rolePresentation":false,"renderedWidth":52,"renderedHeight":52,"naturalWid